-- William Hill Names Ex-Imperial Tobacco Chief Gareth Davis as Its Chairman
-- David Altaner
-- 2010-07-28T13:51:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/william-hill-names-ex-imperial-tobacco-chief-gareth-davis-as-its-chairman.html

          
          
             William Hill Plc , a U.K. bookmaker
with more than 2,300 shops, said it appointed  Gareth Davis ,
former chief executive officer of Imperial Tobacco Group Plc, as
chairman.  
 On Sept. 1, he will replace  Charles Scott , who said in
January he was looking to step down by the end of the year.
Scott had been a director since 1999 and chairman since 2004,
the company said in a Regulatory News Service statement today.  
